\title{Xr Color Management}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{description}{Color spaces and gamuts in XR. sRGB vs DCI-P3 vs Rec.2020, OpenXR swapchain formats, and practical guidance for wide-gamut headsets.}

\subtree{
\title{XR Color Management}
\p{Use when the user asks about:}

\ul{
\li{"best color space" / DCI-P3 / Rec.2020 / sRGB}
\li{why colors look washed out or oversaturated in-headset}
\li{how to ship consistent color across headsets}
}

\subtree{
\title{Ground Truth}
\ul{
\li{\startverb Color gamut coverage (e.g., "96% DCI-P3") is display capability, not color accuracy.\stopverb}
\li{XR runtimes often compose in linear space; apps must be explicit about sRGB vs linear formats.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Practical Defaults}
\ul{
\li{Keep your pipeline sRGB-correct unless you \em{know} your runtime + device support wide-gamut end-to-end.}
\li{Prefer a linear rendering workflow with sRGB textures flagged correctly.}
\li{Validate with in-headset test patterns (ramps, skin tones, near-black, saturation sweeps).}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{OpenXR Notes}
\ul{
\li{Use API-specific sRGB swapchain formats when your render targets are sRGB encoded.}
\li{If you submit linear data in 8-bit formats, banding and incorrect tones are common.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Vendor Extensions (When Available)}
\ul{
\li{Some runtimes expose explicit color space selection (e.g., Meta's \code{\startverb XR_FB_color_space\stopverb} can request P3 / Rec.2020 / Rec.709).}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Troubleshooting Checklist}
\ul{
\li{Confirm you’re not double-applying gamma (too dark/too contrasty) or skipping sRGB decode (too bright/washed).}
\li{Check post-processing: tone mapping, color grading LUTs, exposure auto.}
\li{If the runtime/toolkit offers post-processing (OpenXR Toolkit etc.), use it only to validate hypotheses, not as a permanent substitute for correct pipeline.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Interleave With}
\ul{
\li{\code{\startverb varjo-xr-4\stopverb} for XR-4-specific refresh-rate and Varjo Base settings}
\li{\code{\startverb steamvr-tracking\stopverb} when the XR setup uses Lighthouse base stations}
\li{\code{\startverb visual-design\stopverb} (from plurigrid/asi PR #61) for readable spatial UI color/contrast}
}
}
}